article.headline: Petty's 17 lead Kansas City past North Dakota 65-47
article.description: — Jayson Petty had 17 points in Kansas City's 65-47 victory against North Dakota on Saturday.
article.linkText: Petty's 17 lead Kansas City past North Dakota 65-47
article.story: GRAND FORKS, N.D. -- — Jayson Petty had 17 points in Kansas City's 65-47 victory against North Dakota on Saturday. Petty also contributed seven rebounds for the Roos (11-15, 5-6 Summit League). Khristion Courseault scored 14 points and added five assists. Jamar Brown had 10 points and was 4 of 8 shooting (2 for 5 from 3-point range). The Fightin' Hawks (15-11, 7-4) were led by B.J. Omot, who posted 15 points. North Dakota also got 11 points and nine rebounds from Amar Kuljuhovic. Eli King also had 10 points and six steals. The loss ended a seven-game winning streak for the Fightin' Hawks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
